AN ACT relating to property; prohibiting certain investment
companies from entering into an executory contract for
the purchase of certain residential property under certain
circumstances; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law establishes various requirements relating to the sale of residential
2 property in this State. (Chapters 111 and 113 of NRS) Section 1 of this bill
3 prohibits certain investment companies from entering into an executory contract for
4 the purchase of residential property that is listed for sale unless the property has
5 been so listed for at least 30 days. Section 1 also makes a contract entered into in
6 violation of this prohibition voidable by the seller at any time before the contract is
7 fully executed.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 111 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. An investment company shall not enter into an executory
4 contract for the purchase of residential property that is listed for
5 sale unless the property has been so listed for at least 30 days.
6 2. A contract entered into in violation of subsection 1 is
7 voidable by the seller at any time before the contract is fully
8 executed.
